{"post_content":"<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 1 \u2013 Terraform Fundamentals<\/strong><\/h2>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 1: Terraform Architecture<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What is Terraform?<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Declarative vs. imperative infrastructure management<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>How Terraform works: Providers, state, and execution plans<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Terraform vs. other IaC tools (CloudFormation, Ansible, Pulumi)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 2: Terraform Installation &amp; Lab Setup<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Installing Terraform on different platforms<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Setting up a development environment<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Configuring Terraform CLI and provider authentication<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Lab setup with Terraform and AWS CLI<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 3: Quick Start with Terraform<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Writing your first Terraform configuration<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Initializing, planning, applying, and destroying resources<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Understanding <code>terraform.tfstate<\/code> and state management<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Deploying a simple infrastructure on AWS<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 4: Introduction to AWS<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Overview of AWS services relevant to Terraform<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Setting up AWS credentials and provider configuration<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Deploying an EC2 instance with Terraform<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n<!-- \/wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 2 \u2013 Advanced Terraform &amp; Multi-Cloud Management<\/strong><\/h2>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 5: Variables in Terraform<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Declaring and using input variables<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Variable types and default values<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Sensitive variables and environment overrides<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Using variables to parameterize configurations<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 6: Outputs in Terraform<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Defining and using output values<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Exporting Terraform outputs for other tools<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Creating meaningful outputs for an AWS deployment<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 7: Terraform Modules<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Why use modules?<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Creating reusable modules<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Using public modules from the Terraform Registry<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Refactoring an existing configuration with modules<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 8: Advanced Terraform (Optional)<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Resource dependencies<\/strong> (<code>depends_on<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Local values<\/strong> for better organization<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Data sources<\/strong> for referencing external information<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Count and for_each<\/strong> for dynamic resource creation<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Dynamic blocks<\/strong> for flexible configurations<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Using advanced Terraform features in real-world scenarios<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 9: Provisioning Resources<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Understanding Terraform provisioning<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bootstrapping infrastructure with Ansible<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Automating instance configuration with Terraform &amp; Ansible<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 10: Hands-on Exercise \u2013 Docker &amp; Terraform<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Using Terraform to provision Docker containers<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Deploying a containerized application with Terraform<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 11: Examples for Other Providers<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Managing VMware infrastructure with Terraform<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Working with Terraform and Azure<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n<!-- \/wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Hands-on Labs &amp; Final Project<\/strong><\/h2>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Lab 1<\/strong>: Writing and applying a basic Terraform configuration<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Lab 2<\/strong>: Using variables and outputs for dynamic configurations<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><stron